ReqID.description: Unique ID of a Security Definition Request.

SubTyp.description:
Sub-type qualification/identification of the SecurityType. As an example for SecurityType(167)="REPO", the SecuritySubType="General Collateral" can be used to further specify the type of REPO. 
                    If SecuritySubType is used, then SecurityType is required. 
                    For SecurityType="MLEG" a name of the option or futures strategy name can be specified, such as "Calendar", "Vertical", "Butterfly". 
                    For SecurityType(167)="OPT" the subclassification can be specified, such as "Asian". 
                    For SecurityType(167)="SWAPTION" a value of "Straddle" is used to identify a straddle swaption. 
                    In the context of EU SFTR reporting use the appropriate 4-character code noted in the regulations - "GENE" for general collateral or "SPEC" for specific collateral (without quote marks).

Ccy.description:
Identifies currency used for price or quantity fields, depending on the asset class being traded. CurrencyCodeSource(2897) may be used to disambiguate the code source scheme used, and ISO 4217 is the default scheme if absent. 
                    Absence of this field is interpreted as the default currency for the security as defined by the respective reference data. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible.

Txt.description:
Free format text string 
                    (Note: this field does not have a specified maximum length)

EncTxtLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedText (355) field.

EncTxt.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Text (58) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Text(58) field.

anyOf.description:
Identifier for a trading session. 
                    A trading session spans an extended period of time that can also be expressed informally in terms of the trading day. Usage is determined by market or counterparties. 
                    To specify good for session where session spans more than one calendar day, use TimeInForce = 0 (Day) in conjunction with TradingSessionID(336). 
                    Bilaterally agreed values of data type "String" that start with a character can be used for backward compatibility.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

Optional market assigned sub identifier for a trading phase within a trading session. Usage is determined by market or counterparties. Used by US based futures markets to identify exchange specific execution time bracket codes as required by US market regulations. Bilaterally agreed values of data type "String" that start with a character can be used for backward compatibility
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

PxUOMCcy.description: Indicates the currency of the underlying price unit of measure. Conditionally required when UnderlyingPriceUnitOfMeasure(1424) = Ccy

CpnRt.description:

Issr.description:

ShrtName.description: Short name of the financial instrument. Uses ISO 18774 (FINS) values.

FullName.description: The full normative name of the underlying financial instrument.

NdxPeriod.description: Curve time multiplier for the underlying index.

Desc.description:
Description of the underlying security.

EncUndSecDescLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc (365) field.

EncUndSecDesc.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingSecurityDesc (307) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingSecurityeDesc field.

anyOf.description: The program under which a commercial paper offering is exempt from SEC registration identified by the paragraph number(s) within the US Securities Act of 1933 or as identified below.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

CPRegTyp.description: The registration type of the underlying commercial paper issuance

AllocPct.description: Percent of the Strike Price that this underlying represents.

Qty.description: Unit amount of the underlying security (par, shares, currency, etc.)

CashAmt.description: Cash amount associated with the underlying component.

Px.description: Underlying price associate with a derivative instrument.

DirtPx.description: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket. "Dirty" means it includes accrued interest

EndPx.description: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket at the end of the agreement.

StartVal.description: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the start of the agreement

CurVal.description: Currency value currently attributed to this collateral

EndVal.description: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the end of the agreement

AcrdIntAmt.description: Amount of accrued interest of underlying security.

NumDaysInt.description: Number of days of interest for underlying security.

AdjQty.description: Unit amount of the underlying security (shares) adjusted for pending corporate action not yet allocated.

FxRate.description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute UnderlyingCurrentValue(885) (or market value) from UnderlyingCurrency(318) to Currency(15).

CapValu.description: Maximum notional value for a capped financial instrument

CntraryInstEligInd.description: Identifies whether the option instrument is eligible for contrary instructions at the time of exercise. The contrariness of an instruction will be determined in the context of UnderlyingInTheMoneyCondition(2683). When not specified, the eligibility is undefined or not applicable.

ConstuentWt.description: For a basket, or pool, describes the weight of each of the constituents within the basket. If not provided, it is assumed to be equal weighted.

TotIssuedAmt.description: Specifies the total amount of the issue. Corresponds to the par value multiplied by the number of issued security.

CpnPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

anyOf.description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security. Absence of this field for a bond or an interest bearing security transaction implies a "flat" trade, i.e. no accrued interest determined at time of the transaction.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

CpnOtherDayCnt.description: The industry name of the day count convention not listed in UnderlyingCouponDayCount(1993).

ObligID.description: For a CDS basket or pool identifies the reference obligation.

EqtyID.description: Specifies the equity in which a convertible bond can be converted.

NdxAnxDt.description: The date of a credit default swap index series annex.

NdxAnxSrc.description: The source of a credit default swap index series annex.

SettlNdx.description: In an outright or forward commodity trade that is cash settled this is the index used to determine the cash payment.

SettlNdxLctn.description: This is an optional qualifying attribute of UnderlyingSettlementRateIndex(2284) such as the delivery zone for an electricity contract.

EncExpDescLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingOptionExpirationDesc(2288) field.

EncExpDesc.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingOptionExpirationDesc(2286) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingOptionExpirationDesc(2286).

ProdCmplx.description: Identifies an entire suite of products for a given market. In Futures this may be "interest rates", "agricultural", "equity indexes", etc

SecGrp.description: An exchange specific name assigned to a group of related securities which may be concurrently affected by market events and actions.

SettlOnOpenFlag.description: Indicator to determine if Instrument is Settle on Open.

anyOf.description: The subcategory description of the asset class.
Values "4000" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

AssetTyp.description:
Used to provide more specific description of the asset specified in UnderlyingAssetSubClass(2082). 
                    See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetType for code list of applicable values. ISO 4721 Currency Code values are to be used when specific currency as an asset type is to be expressed. 
                    Other values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.

AsstSubTyp.description:
Used to provide a more specific description of the asset specified in UnderlyingAssetType(2015). 
                    See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetSubType for code list of applicable values.

NthDflt.description: The Nth reference obligation to default in a CDS reference basket. If specified without UnderlyingMthToDefault(2018) the default will trigger a CDS payout. If UnderlyingMthToDefault(2018) is also present then payout occurs between the Nth and Mth obligations to default.

MthDflt.description: The Mth reference obligation to default in a CDS reference basket. When UnderlyingNthToDefault(2017) and UnderlyingMthToDefault(2018) are represented then the CDS payout occurs between the Nth and Mth obligations to default.

SettldMtrxDt.description: Specifies the publication date of the applicable version of the matrix. If not specified, the Standard Terms Supplement defines rules for which version of the matrix is applicable.

StrkMult.description: Used for derivatives. Multiplier applied to the strike price for the purpose of calculating the settlement value.

StrkValu.description: Used for derivatives. The number of shares/units for the financial instrument involved in the option trade.

StrkNdxPnt.description:
The point on the floating rate index curve. Sample values: 
                    M = combination of a number between 1-12 and an "M" for month, e.g. 3M 
                    Y = combination of number between 1-100 and a "Y" for year, e.g. 10Y 
                    10Y-OLD = see above, then add "-OLD" when appropriate 
                    INTERPOLATED = the point is mathematically derived 
                    2/2031 5 3/8 = the point is stated via a combination of maturity month / year and coupon.

StrkNdx.description: Specifies the index used to calculate the strike price.

StrkSpread.description: Specifies the strike price offset from the named index.

StrkPxBndryPrcsn.description: Used in combination with StrikePriceBoundaryMethod(1479) to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

MinPxIncr.description: Minimum price increment for the instrument. Could also be used to represent tick value.

MinPxIncrAmt.description: Minimum price increment amount associated with the UnderlyingMinPriceIncrement(2026). For listed derivatives, the value can be calculated by multiplying UnderlyingMinPriceIncrement(2026) by UnderlyingContractMultiplier(436).

OptPayAmt.description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an option. For binary options this is a fixed amount.

ValSrc.description: Specifies the source of trade valuation data.

ValRefModel.description: Specifies the methodology and/or assumptions used to generate the trade value.

CapPx.description: Used to express the ceiling price of a capped call.

FlrPx.description: Used to express the floor price of a capped put.

FlexInd.description: Used to indicate if a security has been defined as flexible according to "non-standard" means. Analog to CFICode Standard/Non-standard indicator.

FlexProdElig.description: Used to indicate if a product or group of product supports the creation of flexible securities.

NTPosLmt.description: Position Limit in the near-term contract for a given exchange-traded product.

Pool.description: Identifies the mortgage backed security (MBS) / asset backed security (ABS) pool.

CSetMo.description: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle. Must be present for MBS/TBA.

IntAcrl.description: If different from IssueDate and DatedDate

RefTickTblID.description: Spread table code referred by the security or symbol.

ProtctnXIDRef.description: Reference to the protection terms applicable to this entity or obligation. Contains the same XID named string value of the instance in the ProtectionTerms repeating group that applies to this Underlying.

SettlXIDRef.description: Reference to the cash or physical settlement terms applicable to this entity or obligation. Contains the same XID named string value of the instance in the appropriate repeating group that applies to this Underlying.

CmnPxng.description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', it indicates that common pricing applies. Common pricing may be relevant for a transaction that references more than one commodity reference price.

RteChrtr.description: Specific delivery route or time charter average. Applicable to commodity freight contracts.

RndPrcsn.description: Specifies the rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

ExchLookAlike.description: For a share option trade, indicates whether the instrument is to be treated as an 'exchange look-alike'.

AvgLmtPctg.description: The limit of average percentage of individual securities traded in a day or a number of days.

AvgLmtDys.description: Specifies the limitation period for average daily trading volume in number of days.

DpstryRcptInd.description: Indicates whether the underlier is a depository receipt.

OpnUnits.description: The number of units (units of the index or number of securities, par amount of a bond) that constitute the underlier. In the case of a basket swap, this is used to reference both the number of basket units, and the number of each asset components of the basket when these are expressed in absolute terms.

BsktDvsr.description: Specifies the basket divisor amount. This value is normally used to adjust the constituent weight for pricing or to adjust for dividends, or other corporate actions.

XID.description: Identifier for referencing this UnderlyingInstrument from a parent instrument or a convertible instrument.

AltID.description: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource (459) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource.

SymPosNum.description:
Reference to the first or second currency or digital asset in UnderlyingSymbol(311) for FX-style trading. 
                    Conditionally required when one or both symbols in UnderlyingSymbol(311) represent a digital asset.

SecXML.description: XML definition for the underlying security.

Schema.description: The schema used to validate the contents of UnderlyingSecurityXML(1875).

Val.description:
Value of stipulation. 
                    Same values as StipulationValue (234)

PartyID value within an underlying instrument party repeating group. 
                    Same values as PartyID (448)

                    Same values as PartySubID (523)

Dt.description: The date of the event.

Tm.description: The time of the event. To be used in combination with UnderlyingEventDate(1983).

TmUnit.description: Time unit associated with the event.

TmPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the event.

MoYr.description:
Used with derivatives when an event is express as a month-year with optional day or month or week of month. 
                    Format: 
                    YYYYMM (e.g. 199903) 
                    YYYYMMDD (e.g. 20030323) 
                    YYYYMMwN (e.g. 200303w2) for week 
                    A specific date can be appended to the month-year. For instance, if multiple event types exist in the same Year and Month, but actually at a different time, a value can be appended, such as "w" or "w2" to indicate week. Likewise, the day of monty (0-31) can be appended to indicate a specific event date.

Px.description: Predetermined price of issue at event, if applicable.

Txt.description: Free form text to specify comments related to the event.

EncTxtLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingEventText(2073) field.

EncTxt.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingEventText(2071) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingEventText(2071) field.

anyOf.description: The subcategory description of the asset class.
Values "4000" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

Typ.description:
Used to provide more specific description of the asset specified in UnderlyingSecondaryAssetSubClass(2082). 
                    See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetType for code list of applicable values. ISO 4721 Currency Code values are to be used when specific currency as an asset type is to be expressed. 
                    Other values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.

SubTyp.description:
May be used to provide a more specific description of the asset specified in UnderlyingSecondaryAssetType(2083). 
                    See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetSubType for code list of applicable values.

Typ.description:
Specifies the name of the attribute. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Asset_Attribute_Types for code list of applicable asset attribute types.

Val.description: Specifies the value of the attribute.

Lmt.description: Limit or lower acceptable value of the attribute.

OptUndlr.description: Reference to the underlier whose payments are being passed through.

OptPayAmt.description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an event. For binary options this is a fixed amount.

OptPctage.description: Percentage of observed price for calculating the payout associated with the event.

OptCcy.description:
Specifies the currency of the payout amount. 
                    UnderlyingComplexOptPayoutCurrencyCodeSource(2947) may be used to disambiguate the code source scheme used, and ISO 4217 is the default scheme if absent.

Px.description: Specifies the price at which the complex event takes effect. Impact of the event price is determined by the UnderlyingComplexEventType(2046).

PxPctage.description: Specifies the price percentage at which the complex event takes effect. Impact of the event price is determined by the UnderlyingComplexEventType(2046).

PxBndryPrcsn.description: Used in combination with UnderlyingComplexEventPriceBoundaryMethod(2049) to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

Ccy1.description:
Specifies the first or only reference currency of the trade. 
                    UnderlyingComplexEventCurrencyOneCodeSource(2948) may be used to disambiguate the code source scheme used, and ISO 4217 is the default scheme if absent.

Ccy2.description:
Specifies the second reference currency of the trade. 
                    UnderlyingComplexEventCurrencyTwoCodeSource(2949) may be used to disambiguate the code source scheme used, and ISO 4217 is the default scheme if absent.

Rt.description: Specifies the fixed FX rate alternative for FX Quantro options.

FwdPnts.description: FX forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Meth.description:
Specifies the method according to which an amount or a date is determined. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

StrkPx.description: Upper strike price for Asian option feature. Strike percentage for a Strike Spread.

StrkFctr.description: Strike factor for Asian option feature. Upper strike percentage for a Strike Spread.

StrkNum.description: Upper string number of options for a Strike Spread.

CdtEvntXIDRef.description: Reference to credit event table elsewhere in the message.

BizCtr.description:
Specifies the local business center for which the credit event is to be determined. The inclusion of this business center implies that Greenwich Mean Time in Section 3.3 of the 2003 ISDA Credit Derivatives Definitions is replaced by the local time of the specified business center. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

StdSrcs.description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', indicates that ISDA defined Standard Public Sources are applicable.

MinSrcs.description: The minimum number of the specified public information sources that must publish information that reasonably confirms that a credit event has occurred. The market convention is two.

FutPxVal.description: Indicates whether the official settlement price as announced by the related exchange is applicable, in accordance with the ISDA 2002 definitions. Applicable only to futures contracts.

OptPxVal.description: Indicates whether the official settlement price as announced by the related exchange is applicable, in accordance with the ISDA 2002 definitions. Applicable only to options contracts.

XID.description: Identifier of this complex event for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

XIDRef.description: Reference to a complex event elsewhere in the message.

StartDt.description:
The start date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda options. 
                    The start date must always be less than or equal to end date.

EndDt.description:
The end date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda options. 
                    UnderlyingComplexEventEndDate(2056) must always be greater than or equal to UnderlyingComplexEventStartDate(2055).

StartTm.description:
The start time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective. 
                    UnderlyingComplexEventStartTime(2057) must always be less than or equal to UndelryingComplexEventEndTime(2058).

EndTm.description:
The end time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective. 
                    UnderlyingComplexEventEndTime(2058) must always be greater than or equal to UnderlyingComplexEventStartTime(2057).

RefPg.description:
Identifies the reference page from the rate source. 
                    For FX, the reference page to the spot rate is to be used for the reference FX spot rate. 
                    When UnderlyingComplexEventRateSource(41733) = 3 (ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains the value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option.

RefHdg.description: Identifies the reference page heading from the rate source.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the complex event date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted complex event date.

FixngBizCtr.description:
The business center for determining the actual fixing times. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar is used to adjust the event date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

BizCtr.description:
The business center for adjusting dates and times in the schedule or date-time group. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

StartDt.description: The start date of the schedule.

EndDt.description: The end date of the schedule.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the schedule date frequency.

Dt.description:
The averaging date for an Asian option. 
                    The trigger date for a Barrier or Knock option.

Tm.description: The averaging time for an Asian option.

ObsvtnNum.description: Cross reference to the ordinal observation as specified either in the UnderlyingComplexEventScheduleGrp or UnderlyingComplexEventPeriodDateGrp components.

Wt.description: The weight factor to be applied to the observation.

Src.description: A newspaper or electronic news service that may publish relevant information used in the determination of whether or not a credit event has occurred.

Typ.description:
Specifies the type of credit event. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Credit_Event_Types for code list of applicable event types.

Val.description:
The credit event value appropriate to UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventType(41717). 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Credit_Event_Types for applicable event type values.

Ccy.description: Specifies the applicable currency when UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventValue(41718) is an amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Period.description: Time unit multiplier for complex credit events.

RtSrc.description:
Identifies the source of rate information used for credit events. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Credit_Event_Rate_Source for code list of applicable sources.

Ctr.description: A business center whose calendar is used for date adjustment, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

DtUnadj.description: The unadjusted pricing or fixing date.

Dt.description: The adjusted pricing or fixing date.

Tm.description: The local market pricing or fixing time.

TmBizCtr.description: Specifies the business center for determining the pricing or fixing time. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the pricing or fixing date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

MaxDays.description: Specifies the maximum number of market disruption days (commodity or bullion business days) in a contract or confirmation. If none are specified, the maximum number of market disruption days is five (5).

MtrltyPctage.description: Used when a price materiality percentage applies to the price source disruption event and this event has been specified.

MinCtrcts.description: Specifies the minimum futures contracts level that dictates whether or not a 'De Minimis Trading' event has occurred.

Evnt.description:
Specifies the market disruption event. 
                    For commodities see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-market-disruption for values. 
                    For foreign exchange, see http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Market_Disruption_Event for code list of applicable event types.

Typ.description:
Specifies the type of disruption fallback. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-market-disruption-fallback for values.

ID.description: Specifies the identifier value of the security.

enum: Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format)
anyOf.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID(48) value.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

Desc.description: Specifies the description of underlying security.

EncDescLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41874) field.

EncDesc.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41872) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41872).

OpnUnits.description: If there are multiple underlying assets, this specifies the number of units (index or securities) that constitute the underlier of the swap. In the case of a basket swap, this is used to reference both the number of basket units, and the number of each asset components of the basket when these are expressed in absolute terms.

Ccy.description: Specifies the currency if the underlier is a basket. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Dvsr.description: Specifies the basket divisor amount. This value is normally used to adjust the constituent weight for pricing or to adjust for dividends, or other corporate actions.

Desc.description: A description of the option exercise.

EncDescLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingExerciseDesc(41812) field.

EncDesc.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingExerciseDesc(41810) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingExerciseDesc(41810) field.

AutoExerInd.description: Indicates (when 'Y') that exercise is automatic when the strike price is crossed or the underlying trade is in the money.

AutoRt.description: The threshold rate for triggering automatic exercise.

ManNtcBizCtr.description:
Identifies the business center used for adjusting the time for manual exercise notice. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

FallbckExerInd.description: Indicates whether the notional amount of the underlying swap, not previously exercised under the option, will be automatically exercised at the expiration time on the expiration date if at such time the buyer is in-the-money, provided that the difference between the settlement rate and the fixed rate under the relevant underlying swap is not less than one tenth of a percentage point (0.10% or 0.001).

LtdRightCnfmInd.description: Indicates whether the Seller may request the Buyer to confirm its intent to exercise if not done on or before the expiration time on the Expiration date. If true ("Y") specific rules will apply in relation to the settlement mode.

ExerSplitTktInd.description: Indicates in physical settlement of bond and convertible bond options whether the party required to deliver the bonds will divide those to be delivered as notifying party desires to facilitate delivery obligations.

DtUnadj.description: The unadjusted settlement method election date.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the settlement method election date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative settlement method election date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted settlement method election date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the settlement method election unadjusted or relative date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

ErlstOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative earliest exercise date offset.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of exercise dates.

StartDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted start date for calculating periodic exercise dates.

StartDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise start date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

StartDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative exercise start date offset.

StartDt.description: The adjusted start date for calculating periodic exercise dates.

Skip.description: The number of periods in the referenced date schedule that are between each date in the relative date schedule. Thus a skip of 2 would mean that dates are relative to every second date in the referenced schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

NomntnDdln.description: The last date (adjusted) for establishing the option exercise terms.

ErlstTm.description: The earliest time at which notice of exercise can be given by the buyer to the seller (or seller's agent) (i) on the expriation date, in the case of a European style option, (ii) on each Bermuda option exercise date and the expiration date, in the case of a Bermuda style option, (iii) the commencement date to, and including, the expiration date, in the case of an American option.

TmBizCtr.description:
The business center used to determine the locale for option exercise time, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the option exercise dates, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Dt.description: The adjusted or unadjusted option exercise fixed date.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise expiration date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative exercise expiration date offset.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of exercise expiration dates.

TmBizCtr.description:
The business center used to determine the locale for option exercise expiration time, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the option exercise expiration dates, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Dt.description: The adjusted or unadjusted option exercise expiration fixed date.
The date through which the option cannot be exercised without penalty.

Amt.description: Amount to be paid by the buyer of the option if the option is exercised prior to the UnderlyingMakeWholeDate(42888).

Name.description: Identifies the benchmark floating rate index.

Point.description:
The point on the floating rate index curve. 
                    Sample values: 
                    M = combination of a number between 1-12 and an "M" for month, e.g. 3M 
                    Y = combination of number between 1-100 and a "Y" for year, e.g. 10Y 
                    10Y-OLD = see above, then add "-OLD" when appropriate 
                    INTERPOLATED = the point is mathematically derived 
                    2/2031 5 3/8 = the point is stated via a combination of maturity month / year and coupon.

Spread.description: Spread over the floating rate index.

XID.description: Identifier of this UnderlyingStream for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Desc.description: A short descriptive name given to payment stream. Eg. CDS, Fixed, Float, Float2, GBP. The description has no intrinsic meaning but should be arbitrarily chosen by the remitter as a reference.

Ver.description: The stream version identifier when there have been modifications to the contract over time. Helps signal when there are embedded changes.

VerEfctvDt.description: The effective date of the UnderlyingStreamVersion(43083).

NotlXIDRef.description: Cross reference to another UnderlyingStream notional for duplicating its properties.

Notl.description: Notional, or initial notional value for the payment stream. Use SwapSchedule for steps.

Ccy.description: Specifies the currency the UnderlyingStreamNotional(40545) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

NotlDtrmnMeth.description:
Specifies the method for determining the floating notional value for equity swaps. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

NotlPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the swap stream's notional frequency.

TotNotl.description: Specifies the total notional or delivery quantity over the term of the contract.

Txt.description: Free form text to specify additional information or enumeration description when a standard value does not apply.

EncTxtLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingStreamText(40989) field.

EncTxt.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingStreamText(40547) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingStreamText(40547) field.

Base.description: Specifies the general base type of the commodity traded. Where possible, this should follow the naming convention used in the 2005 ISDA Commodity Definitions.

CmdtyTyp.description:
Specifies the type of commodity product. 
                    For coal see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-coal-product-type for values. 
                    For metals see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-metal-product-type for values. 
                    For bullion see http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Bullion_Types for the external code list of bullion types.

ID.description: Specifies the market identifier for the commodity.

enum: Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format)
anyOf.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID(48) value.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

EncDescLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingStreamCommodityDesc(41970) field.

EncDesc.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingStreamCommodityDesc(41968) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingStreamCommodityDesc(41968) field.

DlvryPxngRgn.description: The delivery or pricing region associated with the commodity swap. See http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=660d6a40f836aa6ddf213cba080c5b22&node=ap17.2.43_17.e&rgn=div9 for the external code list.

Ccy.description: Identifies the currency of the commodity asset. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Exch.description: Identifies the exchange where the commodity is traded.

RtSrc.description:
Identifies the source of rate information used for commodities. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Commodity_Rate_Source for code list of applicable sources.

RefPg.description: Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source.

RefHdng.description: Identifies the page heading from the rate source.

DataPrvdr.description:
Specifies the commodity data or information provider. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-information-provider for values.

PxngTyp.description:
Specifies how the pricing or rate setting of the trade is to be determined or based upon. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Commodity_Rate_Pricing_Type for code list of applicable commodity pricing types.

Period.description: Time unit multiplier for the nearby settlement day.

Dt.description: The adjusted commodity delivery date.

Mo.description: Specifies a fixed single month for commodity delivery.

RollPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the commodity delivery date roll.

XID.description: Identifier of this stream commodity for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

XIDRef.description: Reference to a stream commodity elsewhere in the message.

AltID.description: Alternate security identifier value for the commodity.

AltIDSrc.description: Identifies the class or source of the alternate commodity security identifier.

Typ.description:
Specifies the name of the attribute. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Asset_Attribute_Types for code list of applicable asset attribute types.

Val.description: Specifies the value of the attribute.

Lmt.description: The limit or lower acceptable value of the attribute.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the commodity delivery date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ctry.description: Specifies the country where delivery takes place. Uses ISO 3166 2-character country code.

TZ.description:
Commodity delivery timezone specified as "prevailing" rather than "standard" or "daylight". 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Prevailing_Timezones for code list of applicable prevailing timezones.

Notl.description: Specifies the delivery quantity associated with this settlement period.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the settlement period frequency.

PxCcy.description: The currency of the settlement period price. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

XID.description: Identifier of this settlement period for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

XIDRef.description: Cross reference to another settlement period for duplicating its properties.

TotHrs.description: Sum of the hours specified in UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlTimeGrp.

Start.description: The start time for commodity settlement where delivery occurs over time. The time format is specified by the settlement time type.

End.description: The end time for commodity settlement where delivery occurs over time. The time format is specified by the settlement time type.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the effective date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative effective date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted effective date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the underlying instrument's stream's effective, or relative effective, date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the termination date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative termination date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted termination date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the underlying instrument's stream's termination, or relative termination, date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

XID.description: Identifier of this calculation period for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

XIDRef.description: Cross reference to another calculation period for duplicating its properties.

FirstStartDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted first calculation period start date if before the effective date.

FirstStartDt.description: The adjusted first calculation period start date, if it is before the effective date.

FirstReglrStartDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted first start date of the regular calculation period, if there is an initial stub period.

FirstCmpndgEndDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted end date of the initial compounding period.

LastReglrEndDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted last regular period end date if there is a final stub period.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency at which calculation period end dates occur.

BalFirst.description: When specified and set to 'Y', it indicates that the first calculation period should run from the effective date to the end of the calendar period in which the effective date falls (e.g. Jan 15 - Jan 31 if the calculation periods are one month long and effective date is Jan 15.). If 'N' or not specified, it indicates that the first calculation period should run from the effective date for one whole period (e.g. Jan 15 to Feb 14 if the calculation periods are one month long and the effective date is Jan 15.).

CrrctnPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the length of time after the publication of the data when corrections can be made.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the calculation periods, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Dt.description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed calculation period date.

FirstStartDtBizCtr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the underlying instrument's stream's first calculation period start date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

MktRt.description: Used only for credit index trade. This contains the credit spread ("fair value") at which the trade was executed. The market rate varies over the life of the index depending on market conditions. This is the price of the index as quoted by trading desks.

DelayInd.description:
Applicable to credit default swaps on mortgage backed securities to specify whether payment delays are applicable to the fixed amount. 
                    Residential mortgage backed securities typically have a payment delay of 5 days between the coupon date of the reference obligation and the payment date of the synthetic swap. 
                    Commercial mortage backed securities do not typically have a payment delay, with both payment dates (the coupon date of the reference obligation and the payment date of the synthetic swap) being on the 25th of each month.

CshSettlInd.description: Indicates whether cash settlement is applicable.

SettlCcy.description: Specifies the currency that the stream settles in (to support swaps that settle in a currency different from the notional currency). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

anyOf.description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security. Absence of this field for a bond or an interest bearing security transaction implies a "flat" trade, i.e. no accrued interest determined at time of the transaction.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

OtherDayCnt.description: The industry name of the day count convention not listed in UnderlyingPaymentStreamDayCount(40572).

AcrlDays.description: The number of days from the adjusted calculation period start date to the adjusted value date, calculated in accordance with the applicable day count fraction.

Disc.description: Discount rate. The rate is expressed in decimal, e.g. 5% is expressed as 0.05.

anyOf.description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security. Absence of this field for a bond or an interest bearing security transaction implies a "flat" trade, i.e. no accrued interest determined at time of the transaction.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

CmpndgXIDRef.description: Reference to the stream which details the compounding fixed or floating rate.

CmpndgSpread.description: The spread to be used for compounding. Used in scenarios where the interest payment is based on a compounding formula that uses a compounding spread in addition to the regular spread.

InitPrncplExchInd.description: Indicates whether there is an initial exchange of principal on the effective date.

IntrmPrncplExchInd.description: Indicates whether there are intermediate or interim exchanges of principal during the term of the swap.

FnlPrncplExchInd.description: Indicates whether there is a final exchange of principal on the termination date.

FlatRtInd.description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', the Flat Rate is the New Worldwide Tanker Nominal Freight Scale for the Freight Index Route taken at the Trade Date of the transaction "Fixed". If 'N' it is taken on each Pricing Date "Floating".

FlatRtAmt.description: Specifies the actual monetary value of the flat rate when UnderlyingPaymentStreamFlatRateIndicator(41897) = 'Y'.

FlatRtCcy.description: Specifies the currency of the actual flat rate. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

MaxPmtAmt.description: Specifies the limit on the total payment amount.

MaxPmtCcy.description: Specifies the currency of total payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

MaxTxnAmt.description: Specifies the limit on the payment amount that goes out in any particular calculation period.

MaxTxnCcy.description: Specifies the currency of the period payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

CmpndgFixedRt.description: The compounding fixed rate applicable to the payment stream.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of payments.

LastReglrDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted last regular payment date.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when payment dates are relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative payment date offset.

MADts.description: When set to 'Y', it indicates that payment dates are specified in the relevant master agreement.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's payment date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Dt.description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed stream payment date.

DtUnadj.description: The unadjusted final price payment date.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the final price payment date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative final price payment date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted final price payment date.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the reset dates are relative to an anchor date. 
                    If the reset frequency is specified as daily this element must not be included. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for frequency of resets.

InitReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the initial fixing date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

InitPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative initial fixing date offset.

FixngReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the fixing date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

FixngPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative fixing date offset.

Dt.description: The fixing date. Type of date is specified in UnderlyingPaymentStreamFixingDateType(42957).

CutoffPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative rate cut-off date offset.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's reset date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's initial fixing date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's fixing date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Rt.description: The rate applicable to the fixed rate payment stream.

Amt.description: The underlying payment stream's fixed payment amount. In CDS an alternative to UnderlyingPaymentStreamRate(40615).

Ccy.description: Specifies the currency in which UnderlyingPaymentStreamFixedAmount(40616) or UnderlyingPaymentStreamRate(40615) is denominated. Users ISO 4271 currency codes.

FixedAmt.description: Specifies the total fixed payment amount.

FutValNotl.description: The future value notional is normally only required for certain non-deliverable interest rate swaps (e.g. Brazillian Real (BRL) vs. CETIP Interbank Deposit Rate (CDI)). The value is calculated as follows: Future Value Notional = Notional Amount * (1 + Fixed Rate) ^ (Fixed Rate Day Count Fraction). The currency is the same as the stream notional.

FutValDt.description: The adjusted value date of the future value amount.

WorldScaleRt.description: The number of Worldscale points for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a wet voyage charter commodity swap.

CtrctPx.description: The price per relevant unit for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a dry voyage charter or time charter commodity swap.

CtrctPxCcy.description: Specifies the currency of UnderlyingPaymentStreamContractPrice(41907). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Ndx.description: The payment stream's floating rate index.

NdxID.description: Security identifier of the floating rate index.

enum: Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format)
anyOf.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID(48) value.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

NdxPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the underlying instruments floating rate index.

Ndx2.description: The payment stream's second floating rate index.

Ndx2ID.description: Security identifier of the second floating rate index.

enum: Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format)
anyOf.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID(48) value.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

Ndx2Period.description: Secondary time unit multiplier for the payment streams floating rate index curve.

NdxLctn.description: Specifies the location of the floating rate index.

NdxLvl.description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD index level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

RefLvl.description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD reference level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

RefLvlZero.description: When set to 'Y', it indicates that the weather reference level equals zero.

RtMult.description: A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. A multiplier schedule is expressed as explicit multipliers and dates. In the case of a schedule, the step dates may be subject to adjustment in accordance with any adjustments specified in the calculationPeriodDatesAdjustments. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This element should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the stream.

SpreadCcy.description: Specifies the currency of the floating rate spread. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

RtFctr.description: The number to be multiplied by the derived floating rate of the underlying's payment stream in order to arrive at the payment rate. If omitted, the floating rate conversion factor is 1.

CapRt.description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The cap rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

FlrRt.description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A floor rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

InitRt.description: The initial floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. This is assumed to be the first required reset rate for the first regular calculation period. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. An initial rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

LastResetRt.description: The floating rate determined at the most recent reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

FnlRt.description: The floating rate determined at the final reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

FnlRtPrcsn.description: Specifies the rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

CalcLagPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the calculation lag duration.

FirstObsvtnDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted initial price observation date.

FirstObsvtnReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the initial price observation date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

FirstObsvtnOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative first observation date offset.

FirstObsvtnDt.description: The adjusted initial price observation date.

PxngDayCnt.description: The number of days over which pricing should take place.

PxngClndr.description:
Specifies the business calendar to use for pricing. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-business-calendar for values.

LagPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the inflation lag period. The lag period is the offsetting period from the payment date which determines the reference period for which the inflation index is observed.

PublctnSrc.description: The current main publication source such as relevant web site or a government body.

InitLvl.description: Initial known index level for the first calculation period.

FallbckBond.description: Indicates whether a fallback bond as defined in the 2006 ISDA Inflation Derivatives Definitions, sections 1.3 and 1.8, is applicable or not. If not specified, the default value is "Y" (True/Yes).

UndlrRefID.description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

RtnRtNotlReset.description: Indicates whether the term "Equity Notional Reset" as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions is applicable ("Y") or not.

LinkInitLvl.description: Price level at which the correlation or variance swap contract will strike.

LinkClsngLvl.description: Indicates whether the correlation or variance swap contract will ("Y") strike off the closing level of the default exchange traded contract or not.

LinkExpngLvl.description: Indicates whether the correlation or variance swap contract will ("Y") strike off the expiring level of the default exchange traded contract or not.

LinkEstTrdgDays.description: The expected number of trading days in the variance or correlation swap stream.

LinkStrkPx.description: The strike price of a correlation or variance swap stream.

LinkMaxBndry.description:
Specifies the maximum or upper boundary for variance or strike determination. 
                    For a variation swap stream all observations above this price level will be excluded from the variance calculation. 
                    For a correlation swap stream the maximum boundary is a percentage of the strike price.

LinkMinBndry.description:
Specifies the minimum or lower boundary for variance or strike determination. 
                    For a variation swap stream all observations below this price level will be excluded from the variance calculation. 
                    For a correlation swap stream the minimum boundary is a percentage of the strike price.

LinkNumDataSeries.description: Number of data series for a correlation swap. Normal market practice is that correlation data sets are drawn from geographic market areas, such as America, Europe and Asia Pacific. Each of these geographic areas will have its own data series to avoid contagion.

VarncCap.description: Indicates the scaling factor to be multiplied by the variance strike price thereby making variance cap applicable.

DaysAdjmt.description: Indicates whether the contract specifies that the notional should be scaled by the number of days in range divided by the estimate trading days or not. The number of "days in range" refers to the number of returns that contribute to the realized volatility.

ExchCtrctRefID.description: References a contract listed on an exchange through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

VegaNotlAmt.description: Vega Notional represents the approximate gain/loss at maturity for a 1% difference between RVol (realised volatility) and KVol (strike volatility). It does not necessarily represent the Vega risk of the trade.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's pricing dates, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

DayNum.description: The occurrence of the day of week on which pricing takes place.

Dt.description: An adjusted or unadjusted fixed pricing date.

Ccy.description: The currency in which the formula amount is denominated. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

CcyDtrmnMeth.description:
Specifies the method according to which the formula amount currency is determined. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

RefAmt.description:
Specifies the reference amount when this term either corresponds to the standard ISDA Definition (either the 2002 Equity Definition for the Equity Amount, or the 2000 Definition for the Interest Amount), or refers to a term defined elsewhere in the swap document. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Payment_Amount_Relative_To for code list of reference amounts.

FrmlaLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormula(42982) field.

Frmla.description: Contains an XML representation of the formula. Defined for flexibility in choice of language (MathML, OpenMath or text).

Desc.description: A description of the math formula in UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormula(42982).

FrmlaImgLen.description: Length in bytes of the UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormulaImage(42948) field.

FrmlaImg.description: Image of the formula image when represented through an encoded clip in base64Binary.

RnvstmntInd.description: Indicates whether the dividend will be reinvested.

UndlrRefID.description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in a separate instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

ExtrordCcy.description: The currency in which the excess dividend is denominated. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

ExtrordDtrmnMeth.description:
Specifies the method in which the excess amount is determined. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

AcrlFixedRt.description:
The dividend accrual fixed rate per annum expressed as a decimal. 
                    A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

NumNdxUnits.description: The number of index units applicable to dividends.

CshPctage.description:
Declared cash dividend percentage. 
                    A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

CshEqvlntPctage.description: Declared cash-equivalent dividend percentage. A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

SpeclDividendInd.description: Indicates whether special dividends are applicable.

MtrlDividendInd.description: Indicates whether material non-cash dividends are applicable.

ExchDividendInd.description: Indicates whether option exchange dividends are applicable.

AddtnlDividendInd.description: Indicates whether additional dividends are applicable.

AllDividendInd.description: Represents the European Master Confirmation value of 'All Dividends' which, when applicable, signifies that, for a given Ex-Date, the daily observed share price for that day is adjusted (reduced) by the cash dividend and/or the cash value of any non-cash dividend per share (including extraordinary dividends) declared by the issuer.

Seq.description: Defines the ordinal dividend period. E.g. 1 = First period, 2 = Second period, etc.

StartDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted date on which the dividend period will begin.

EndDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted date on which the dividend period will end.

UndlrRefID.description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

StrkPx.description: Specifies the fixed strike price of the dividend period.

ValDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted dividend period valuation date.

ValDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the dividend period valuation date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

ValDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative dividend period valuation date offset.

ValDt.description: The adjusted dividend period valuation date.

PmtDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted dividend period payment date.

PmtDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the dividend period payment date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

PmtDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative dividend period payment date offset.

PmtDt.description: The adjusted dividend period payment date.

XID.description: Identifier for linking this stream dividend period to an underlier through an instance of RelatedInstrumentGrp.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's dividend period date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the FX trigger date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative FX trigger date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted FX trigger date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's FX trigger date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ndx.description: The dividend accrual floating rate index.

NdxPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the dividend accrual floating rate index curve.

RtMult.description: A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the contract.

Spread.description: The basis points spread from the index specified in UnderlyingDividendFloatingRateIndex(42801).

CapRt.description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. It is only required where the floating rate is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

FlrRt.description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate. The rate is expressed as a decimal, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

InitRt.description: The initial floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. This is assumed to be the first required reset rate for the first regular calculation period. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. The initial rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

FnlRtPrcsn.description: Specifies the rounding precision of the final rate in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the accrual payment date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative accrual payment date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted accrual payment date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's dividend accrual payment date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

CommCcy.description: Specifies the currency the commission amount is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

DtrmnMeth.description:
Specifies the method by which the underlier prices are determined. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

AmtReltv.description:
Specifies the reference amount when the return rate amount is relative to another amount in the trade. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Payment_Amount_Relative_To for code list of relative amounts.

QteTyp.description:
Specifies the type of the measure applied to the return rate's asset, e.g. valuation, sensitivity risk. This could be an NPV, a cash flow, a clean price, etc. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/asset-measure for values.

QteUnit.description:
Specifies the units that the measure is expressed in. If not specified, the default is a price/value in currency units. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/price-quote-units for values.

QteCcy.description: Specifies the currency the return rate quote is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

QteCcyTyp.description:
Specifies the type of currency, e.g. settlement currency, base currency, etc., that the quote is reported in. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/reporting-currency-type for values.

QteTm.description: The time when the quote is to be generated.

QteDt.description: The date when the quote is to be generated.

QteExpTm.description: The time when the quote ceases to be valid.

QteBizCtr.description:
The business center calendar used for adjustments associated with UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteTimeType(43047) or UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteTime(43048) and UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteDate(43049), e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

QteExch.description: Specifies the exchange (e.g. stock or listed futures/options exchange) from which the quote is obtained.

QteModel.description:
Specifies the pricing model used to evaluate the underlying asset price. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/pricing-model for values.

CshFlow.description:
Specifies the type of cash flows, e.g. coupon payment, premium fee, settlement fee, etc. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/cashflow-type for values.

ValTm.description: The time at which the calculation agent values the underlying asset.

ValTmBizCtr.description:
The business center calendar used for adjustments associated with UnderlyingReturnRateValuationTimeType(43055) or UnderlyingReturnRateValuationTime(43056) , e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Px.description: Specifies the price of the underlying swap asset.

Ccy.description: Specifies the currency of the price of the underlying swap asset. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

CcySym.description: Specifies the currency pair for the FX conversion expressed using the CCY1/CCY2 convention. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

FxRt.description: The rate of exchange between the two currencies specified in UnderlyingReturnRateFXCurrencySymbol(43031).

RefPg.description:
Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source. 
                    For FX, the reference page to the spot rate to be used for the reference FX spot rate. 
                    When UnderlyingReturnRateInformationSource(43061) = 3 (ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains the value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. 
                    See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option

RefHdng.description: Identifies the page heading from the rate source.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the return rate valuation dates are relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative return rate valuation date offset.

StartDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted start date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

StartDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the return rate valuation start date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

StartDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative return rate valuation start date offset.

StartDt.description: The adjusted start date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

EndDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted end date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

EndDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the return rate valuation end date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

EndDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative return rate valuation end date offset.

EndDt.description: The adjusted end date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency at which return rate valuation dates occur.

Dt.description: The return rate valuation date. Type of date is specified in UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateType(43073).

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the return rate valuation unadjusted or relative dates, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ndx.description: The payment stream's compounding floating rate index.

NdxPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the payment stream's compounding floating rate index curve period.

RtMult.description: A rate multiplier to apply to the compounding floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the stream.

Spread.description: The basis points spread from the index specified in UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRateIndex(42923).

CapRt.description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the compounding floating rate. It is only required where the compounding floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

FlrRt.description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the compounding floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the compounding floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate. The rate is expressed as a decimal, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

InitRt.description: The initial compounding floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. The initial rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

FnlRtPrcsn.description: Specifies the compounding floating rate rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the compounding dates are relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative compounding date offset.

Skip.description: The number of periods in the "RelativeTo" schedule that are between each date in the compounding schedule. A skip of 2 would mean that compounding dates are relative to every second date in the "RelativeTo" schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency at which compounding dates occur.

FirstDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted first date of the compounding schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

LastDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted last date of the compounding schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the payment stream compounding dates, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Dt.description: The compounding date. Type of date is specified in UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDateType(42903).

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the compounding start date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.
